4. Removing Elements
To remove an element from a list, we can use the remove() method. This method is overloaded to perform multiple operations based on different parameters.
a. remove(Object o): Removes the first occurrence of the specified object from the list.
b. remove(int index): Removes the element at the specified index and shifts subsequent elements left.

